ages</media:credit><media:text type="plain">An outbreak of &#34;severe acute respiratory illness&#34; on board a cruise ship in the Atlantic has left two people dead and a third in intensive care in Johannesburg.</media:text><media:description type="plain">The MV Hondius cruise ship off the port of Praia, Cape Verde on May 3, 2026. </media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260504-hondius-cruise-ship-mb-1118-881a58.jpg" height="1667" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Mon, 04 May 2026 12:57:19 GMT</pubDate><title>Cruise ship at center of deadly hantavirus outbreak refused permission to dock</title><updateDate>Mon, 04 May 2026 12:57:19 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Doha Madani</dc:creator><dateTimeWritten>Mon, 04 May 2026 10:20:00 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>The team behind Philadelphia’s World Cup host committee hopes to showcase the city’s history and notorious enthusiasm for sports to the thousands of expected visitors this summer.</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/sports/soccer/philadelphia-world-cup-fan-experience-fifa-rcna342497</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/sports/soccer/philadelphia-world-cup-fan-experience-fifa-rcna342497</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-04/260429-fifa-philadelphia-vl-1213p-ec028e.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1333" width="2000"><media:credit>Erica Denhoff</media:credit><media:text type="plain">A general view of signage with the FIFA World Cup 26 Philadelphia logo on the exterior of the Wells Fargo Center </media:text><media:description type="plain">FIFA World Cup 26 Philadelphia signage on the exterior of the Wells Fargo Center in Philadelphia in 2025.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-04/260429-